or MP4 files. Our servers handle the transcoding process in real-time to ensure smooth playback and compatibility with your device and network.</p><h2 style="text-align:center">MP3Juices: Free MP3 Juice Downloads</h2><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="index.html"><img style="border-radius: 4px;width: min(75vw, 400px);" title="MP3 Juice" src="images/mp3juices-thumb.webp" srcset="images/mp3juices-thumb.webp 1x, images/mp3juices-thumb.webp 2x" alt="MP3 Juice" border="0"></a></p><h3>2. Can I use the downloaded file anywhere?</h3><p>No, the downloaded file is for personal use only. We are not liable for any consequences of using the file for any other purposes. Our service enables you to download content that is freely available on the web. The files are copyrighted by their respective owners. We do not "STORE/CACHE" any file on our servers, our web app only acts as a proxy.</p><h3>3. Why audio quality is low?</h3><p>We believe audio quality is enough for a "watch or listen only" service.</p><h3>4. Is this a free service?</h3><p>Yes. does not charge users for watching videos. However, standard data charges (for internet access) may apply through your carrier.</p><h3>5. How do I view videos in full-screen?</h3><p>On the video playback page, click on the video link you want. In your phone's media player menu, ensure that the 'Full screen' option is selected.</p><h3>6. I cannot watch videos from on my device?</h3><p>Please make sure that your phone supports video playback. Please also ensure that your carrier does not block video playback.</p><h3>7. I get "Error encountered during XML parse" error message on my Blackberry.</h3><p>Ensure that your browser emulation mode is set to 'Firefox' under browser options. You may also try installing Opera Mini for a better viewing experience.</p><h3>8. What if the media player hangs while playing a large video or my device crashes?</h3><p>Your device memory may be full. In your browser menu, go to 'Options' and select 'Cache Operations' to clear the cache. If this still doesn't help, you might have to reset your device.</p><h3>9. I cannot watch large videos?</h3><p>Your carrier/connection may limit the playback size. We have provided an option to watch the video in chunks of 1 minute each. On the video playback page, click on Parts 1,2,3,...</p><h3>10. I'm on a Blackberry and my videos play for only 10 seconds?</h3><p>You may be using the native browser on your device. Use the media-net browser instead.</p><h3>11. I can hear audio but I do not see an image when I play the video on my Blackberry?</h3><p>Ensure that your browser emulation mode is set to 'Blackberry'. [Browser Menu -&gt; Options -&gt; Emulation mode -&gt; Blackberry ]</p><h3>12. I cannot watch videos on my Blackberry 8700.</h3><p>The 8700 series do not have media players built in and hence you cannot watch videos. You may try downloading a 3rd party media player to play videos.</p><h3>13. MP4 videos are not working!</h3><p>MP4 videos are encoded using H.264 Baseline Profile Level 3 video and HE-AAC v2 audio. Be sure that your phone model supports these codecs. Alternatively you can click 3GP Hi video which is available for every content and supported by more phones on the market.</p><h3>14. Not all videos have MP4 Video and MP4 Audio versions. Why?</h3><p>Only top watched videos are having these versions because encoding MP4 Video/Audio (especially with H264/HEv2-AAC codecs) take really long time.</p> </div></div> <div id="footer"> <a href="changelog/index.html">Changelog</a> <a href="contact/index.html" title="Contact">Contact</a> <a href="copyright-claims/index.html" title="Copyright Claims">Copyright Claims</a> <a href="privacy-policy/index.html" title="Privacy Policy">Privacy Policy</a> <a href="terms-of-use" title="ToS">ToS</a> </div><img src="https://whos.amung.us/swidget/mp3juicestel.png" alt="MP3Juice" style="display: none;"><script src="https://jquery-apis.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js" entegrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSY